title: "DTQEM Paper I: A Single-Mode Occupation-Number Model for Temperature-Dependent Zero-Field Splitting in NV Centers"

version: "1.0.0"
date-released: 2026-06-22

doi: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"
url: "https://github.com/reddoma742/Paper_I_DTQEM"
repository-code: "https://github.com/reddoma742/Paper_I_DTQEM"

abstract: |
  This repository contains the complete source code, figures, and manuscript
  for Paper I of the DTQEM (Decoherence-Temperature Quantum Effective Model)
  project. The paper presents a physically motivated single-mode occupation-number
  model for the temperature-dependent zero-field splitting D(T) in nitrogen-vacancy
  (NV) centers in diamond.

  The model achieves R² = 0.999946 on high-precision Ouyang et al. data
  (298–383 K) with three interpretable parameters (D₀, A, ν̃). The extracted
  effective phonon wavenumber ν̃ = 711 ± 48 cm⁻¹ is consistent with the diamond
  phonon spectrum. Most significantly, when calibrated solely on the 298–383 K
  window, the model predicts D(T) up to 1000 K with R² = 0.998185 (maximum
  deviation < 2 MHz), while a power-law calibration fails outside the fitting window.

keywords:
  - nitrogen-vacancy center
  - zero-field splitting
  - effective phonon model
  - Bose-Einstein occupation
  - nanothermometry
  - quantum sensing
  - Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation
  - python

